, processes and standard operating procedures (SOPs)...<a href=\"http://www.oimgroup.com/products-services/operations-management/operations-management-interventions.php\">Read more</a></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Business systems:</strong> We project manage the implementation of IT systems to meet your business architecture requirements...<a href=\"http://www.oimgroup.com/products-services/operations-management/information-technology-management.php\">Read more</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>THE OIM DIFFERENCE</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>OIM’s offering is unique in that we have a multidisciplinary team of consultants with decades of experience in operations management, organisational performance and people management.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>This offers seamless integration of the following key areas that relate to your business architecture:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strategic planning</li>\r\n	<li>Organisational and operational structures</li>\r\n	<li>Scorecards</li>\r\n	<li>Processes and productivity standards</li>\r\n	<li>Project management of information systems</li>\r\n	<li>Competency profiling</li>\r\n	<li>Reward strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Change management and change communication</li>\r\n	<li>Individual performance management</li>\r\n	<li>Operational communication structures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>", "Business Architecture", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "412-revision-v1", "", "", "2013-10-16 14:11:39", "2013-10-16 12:11:39", "", "412", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/news/uncategorized/412-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("422", "3", "2013-10-16 14:13:35", "2013-10-16 12:13:35", "<p>As a chartered accountant and financial director of OIM, Marié has played a crucial rule in the restructuring and centralisation of the finance function, setting up new business ventures and negotiating shareholding contracts. </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n                    <p>After completing her studies, Marié worked as a trainee accountant at prestigious auditing firm PricewaterhouseCoopers for three years. In March 2009 she was appointed assistant manager at the company, dealing with major clients such as Remgro, Shoprite and Agrico Machinery.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>At OIM</h2>\r\n                    <p>Mari&eacute; joined OIM in January 2010 as financial manager and stepped into the position of financial director in November the same year. Since her appointment she has made a marked impact and currently plays a key role in new-business development, such as the joint venture OIM Umbono Mining Solutions and the one-company initiative early in 2013. </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>Hons B Accounting – Stellenbosch University (2005)</li>\r\n                        <li>Postgraduate Diploma in Auditing (APT) – University of Cape Town (2007)</li>\r\n                        <li>Registered with the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\n                    <p>Mari&eacute; gives expression to her creative side by painting portraits and landscapes, a hobby she has practised since her teenage years. She also enjoys mountain biking with her husband and experimenting in the kitchen.</p>", "Mari&eacute; Burger", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "mari-burger", "", "", "2013-10-22 16:24:18", "2013-10-22 14:24:18", "", "0", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=422", "4", "team_members", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("424", "3", "2013-10-16 14:19:15", "2013-10-16 12:19:15", "<strong>An operations review is a quick, reliable way to identify areas of operational constraint and map a solution.</strong>\r\n\r\nOIM’s operations management consultants have developed a proven approach to conduct this review in <strong>two to four weeks</strong>. This approach has been successfully applied at numerous businesses and in several sectors since 1996.\r\n<h2>OUR OFFERING</h2>\r\nThe short review analyses areas such as productivity, process unit costs, quality levels, waste and the impact of machine and labour downtime. It consists of three phases:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/image_operations_review.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-955\" alt=\"image_operations_review\" src=\"http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/image_operations_review.png\" width=\"570\" height=\"201\" /></a>\r\n\r\nOnce the review has been completed, OIM presents the results, highlights the areas for improvement, recommends actions to address them and submits projected cost benefits.\r\n<h2>THE OIM DIFFERENCE</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OIM\'s operations management team has experience in both business processes and systems management, providing clients with a comprehensive service and depth of knowledge in these fields.</li>\r\n	<li>With a track recording date back to the late 90’s, the team has experience in various industries including manufacturing, mining, retail, financial services and local government sectors. Some of the clients who’ve benefited from our operational solutions are Allan Gray, Assmang Khumani Mine, Metropolitan, Meatco and Glacier by Sanlam.</li>\r\n	<li>We pride ourselves in our ability to design customised interventions for clients, with a proven ability to identify inefficiencies and scope relevant solutions.</li>\r\n	<li>When designing these interventions, we draw on a range of methodologies and best practices to create the appropriate structures, processes and systems for effective strategy execution and operations management.</li>\r\n	<li>If required, clients also have access to the expertise embedded in the rest of OIM’s specialist areas, namely organisational improvement and people management. This includes strategic planning, business architecture, employee engagement, leadership development and employee relations. All of these solutions are seamlessly implemented by specialists in the core business areas.</li>\r\n</ul>", "Operations Review", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "operations-review", "", "", "2013-10-27 13:51:23", "2013-10-27 11:51:23", "", "0", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=products_services&#038;p=424", "0", "products_services", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("425", "3", "2013-10-16 14:15:05", "2013-10-16 12:15:05", "<p>With a consulting career spanning 23 years, Ben Nel can lay claim to extensive expertise in production management optimisation, process analysis and improvement, process re-engineering and call centre optimisation in most industries.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n                    <p>Ben has served in senior management positions at various consulting firms over the years. This includes being partner at Rethink Management Consulting where his list of leading clients included Woolworths Financial Services, Allan Gray, Glacier Financial Services, Metropolitan Life, Brandhouse, Old Mutual Client Services and Employee Benefits, Liberty Corporate Benefits, Clicks and Truworths. He also worked as consultant at Alexander Proudfoot for three years, where his projects included a business improvement and call centre implementation in Melbourne, Australia. Prior to this he had been a business analyst at Sanlam’s Process Analysis and Improvement Department for four years.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>At OIM</h2>\r\n                    <p>As a director of OIM, Ben currently serves on the board. He is also a founder of the Operations Solutions division that was established in July 2010, and currently oversees all the operations management interventions.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>BComm Honours in Business Management – Stellenbosch University (1997)</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\n                    <p>An avid mountain biker, Ben spends much of his free time on the outdoor trails around Stellenbosch, Tokai, Grabouw and Durbanville, and also likes to challenge his children to a game of PlayStation Move. He recently attempted skateboarding, but won’t be doing that again anytime soon . . .</p>", "Ben Nel", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "ben-nel", "", "", "2013-10-22 16:24:54", "2013-10-22 14:24:54", "", "0", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=425", "5", "team_members", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("427", "3", "2013-10-16 14:17:01", "2013-10-16 12:17:01", "<p>Since 1988 Chris Jacobs has consulted widely in a range of industries, both locally and abroad. During this time he has gained an impressive 21 years’ experience in OIM’s proven performance improvement methodology. </p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>His fields of expertise include conflict resolution, management-union relations, the establishment of employee engagement tools, strategic planning and execution, and diversity management. He has successfully lead projects in these areas at clients such as Anglo Platinum, Anglo Gold, Samancor, Khumani Assmang, Oceana, Woolworths, Tiger Brands, British American Tobacco, Distell and Barloworld. He was, for example, the chief facilitator of the peace process during the much publicised violence and disruptions at Anglo Platinum in 1997. To this day Anglo Platinum is using some of the measures Chris and his team put in place.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n                    <p>Chris’ interest in labour relations matters was first sparked in 1988 – soon after graduation – when he spent five years as a research analyst in labour relations. As such he was heavily involved with trade union/management relations and conflict resolution.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>At OIM</h2>\r\n                    <p>Since joining OIM in 1992, Chris has consulted in among others the mining, food, wine and spirits, tobacco, fishing, chemical, petroleum, laboratory and services industries. This included managing operational and organisational improvement assignments in the UK, USA, Spain and several African countries. It resulted in the OIM methodology being introduced in countries such as France, Germany, Italy and Portugal.</p>\r\n                    <p>Over the years Chris has played a major role in OIM product development, in particular INVOCOMS® and client-specific applications, and the training and development of new OIM consultants.</p>\r\n                    <p>He has served as director of the company for numerous years and also forms part of the management team of OIM’s Performance Improvement division.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>Higher Education Diploma and BA Honours – Stellenbosch University (1987 and 1986) </li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\n                    <p>An outdoors person, Chris enjoys scuba diving and everything that involves water, nature and good times with close friends.</p>", "Chris Jacobs", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "chris-jacobs", "", "", "2013-10-22 16:25:35", "2013-10-22 14:25:35", "", "0", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=427", "6", "team_members", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("430", "3", "2013-10-16 14:18:14", "2013-10-16 12:18:14", "<p>Mechanical engineer Christian Kaiser has been involved in operational improvement consulting since 2006. His areas of expertise include continuous improvement, process engineering and improvement, and Lean Six Sigma implementations. He also boasts eight years’ research experience in production design.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n                    <p>Prior to joining OIM Christian was a partner at the operational consulting firm Burger, Kaiser and Associates and a principal consultant at Rethink Management Consulting. During this time he worked on a range of business performance improvement projects, including business process automation, process engineering and improvement, Lean Six Sigma implementations, business process management (BPM) implementation, business analysis and project management.</p>\r\n                    <p>Upon graduation he also spent eight years as senior researcher at Element Six, responsible for product design, the development of material and the transfer of research products into full production. During this time he spent several months working in Sweden and regularly interacted with colleagues on German and Swedish plants. Much of this work involved process analysis and redesign and it sparked his interest in the consulting field.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>At OIM</h2>\r\n                    <p>Since April 2013 Christian serves on OIM’s executive committee and is a principal consultant in operations solutions. In addition to client implementations, Christian is closely involved with the design of new operations management product offerings, primarily in the area of continuous improvement.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>BSc in Mechanical Engineering (cum laude) – University of the Witwatersrand (1997)</li>\r\n                        <li>Graduate Diploma in Engineering – University of the Witwatersrand (2007)</li>\r\n                        <li>Six Sigma Black Belt training – BMG Africa (2006)</li>\r\n                        <li>TRIZ Theory of Inventive Problem Solving – BMG Africa (2006)</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\n                    <p>A major outdoors enthusiast, you’ll often find Christian trail running, motorcycling and hiking with his family in his spare time.</p>", "Christian Kaiser", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "christian-kaiser", "", "", "2013-10-22 16:26:07", "2013-10-22 14:26:07", "", "0", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=430", "7", "team_members", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("432", "3", "2013-10-16 14:19:32", "2013-10-16 12:19:32", "<p>With over 20 years’ experience, Francois Bedeker has spent most of his career in management consulting. As an industrial engineer with an MComm in business management, he has been involved in projects covering business strategy, procurement transformation, operations management, facilities deployment, value engineering, productivity improvement, process re-engineering, systems integration, business modelling, supply chain management and the development of business reporting and measurement. He has consulted in a range of industries including financial services, manufacturing, mining, utilities, chemicals, transport, agriculture, food, textile and logistics.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>In addition to consulting, Francois has experience as a technical manager responsible for product development, production process improvement and quality assurance with a manufacturing concern, and has managed the internal consulting unit of a logistics business. </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Work Experience</h2>\r\n                    <p>Between 1999 and 2010, Francois held senior positions at two management consulting firms, Rethink Management Consulting and Atos KPMG Consulting. During this time his responsibilities included managing workstreams for strategy development and performance improvement, scorecard development, the development of methodologies for strategic procurement and value-based management, diagnostics toolsets, business process re-engineering, business case development, and scheduling systems to optimise fleet utilisation. During this period he also gained experience in logistics optimisation as the 4PL manager at Value Logistics from March 2004 to February 2006.</p>\r\n\r\n                    <p>Prior to this he was production and product development manager at Power Profile, served as consultant at CSIR (Mikomtek) and worked as senior consultant/productivity analyst at the National Productivity Institute for six years. </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>At OIM</h2>\r\n                    <p>After the establishment of the Operations Solutions division in July 2010, Francois joined OIM and was elected a director of the wider OIM group in April 2013.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>Qualifications</h2>\r\n                    <p>\r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>MComm in Business Management – University of Johannesburg (former RAU) (1996)</li>\r\n                        <li>BEng – University of Pretoria (1989)</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                    </p>\r\n                    \r\n                    <h2>On A Personal Note</h2>\r\n                    <p>As a self-proclaimed family man, Francois spends most of his free time with his wife and two sons, travelling to remote locations on overland trips.</p>", "Francois Bedeker", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "francois-bedeker", "", "", "2013-10-22 16:26:58", "2013-10-22 14:26:58", "", "0", "http://staging.fishgate.co.za/OIM/?post_type=team_members&#038;p=432", "8", "team_members", "", "0");
